threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, OpenRISC, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ARMv7 ELF binary is a malicious botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt. It exhibits several characteristic behaviors: it implements a single-instance lock via '/tmp/.bot_lock', performs process scanning and enumeration using the /proc filesystem to target common system services (e.g., sshd, rsyslogd, systemd), and contains hardcoded HTTP attack templates (GET, POST, HEAD) with a Chrome User-Agent for DDoS operations. The binary utilizes direct syscalls and features a large 4.3MB .bss section, typical of IoT malware designed for runtime data caching and persistence.
